OL,6,FAt the time Kogan was announced as the
OL,7,Fpreferred candidate, he said: "Across
OL,8,Fthe country millions of us share a
OL,9,Fpassion for football, a game that is
OL,10,Fnot only part of our national heritage
OL,11,Fbut one of our most valuable cultural
OL,12,Fexports.
OL,14,F"Our professional clubs, whatever
OL,15,Ftheir size, are a source of local and
OL,16,Fnational pride. They generate economic
OL,17,Fgrowth and investment, unite
OL,18,Fcommunities, and create shared
OL,19,Fexperiences and memories that
OL,20,Ftranscend generations.
